.START 

Arizona Public Service Co., the utility unit of Pinnacle West Capital Corp., said it called for the redemption Nov. 15 of $3 million of its approximately $51 million of 10.6%, first mortgage bonds due 2000.
The redemption, pursuant to a mandatory sinking fund, is at par, plus accrued interest.
The securities to be redeemed will be chosen by lottery.
Affected bondholders will be notified by mail on or before Oct. 16, the company said. 

